Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.680 --> 00:00:04.680
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, DC.

00:00:18.380 --> 00:00:20.450
&gt;&gt; Travis Hensley: Though Robert
Burns is most commonly known

00:00:20.450 --> 00:00:23.390
as Scotland's national poet,
he also made a big impact

00:00:23.390 --> 00:00:27.110
in the United States of
America during the late 18th

00:00:27.110 --> 00:00:29.040
and 19th centuries.

00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:32.360
In this lecture, Dr. Sood
discusses the complex way

00:00:32.360 --> 00:00:36.220 position:56%
that multifaceted cultural memory
of Robert Burns in the United States

00:00:36.220 --> 00:00:39.000
of America from 1800 to 1900.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:41.510
Please join me in welcoming
Arun Sood.

00:00:41.510 --> 00:00:48.790
